	<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a itemprop="url" href="http://ottopress.com/2011/photo-gallery-primer/comment-page-1/#comment-8745">
		<time itemprop="dateCreated" datetime="2011-06-08T14:44:59+00:00">June 8, 2011 at 2:44 pm</time></a>	</div>

	<div itemprop="text"><p>My goal is really more to get theme authors to add support for this in their own themes. Implementing this sort of thing as a plugin would defeat the purpose. A photo gallery isn&#8217;t an add-on, it&#8217;s built into WordPress. It&#8217;s an integral part of a site, for certain types of sites. It should look like the theme looks, not look like some bolt-on gallery.</p>
</div>

